    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Dialog: Plane</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2" style="page-break-before:always;">Add / Edit Plane</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Model-elements(Model)-AddPlane">Model Editor &gt; Add Plane</link> and <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-ModelElements(Mechanism)-AddPlane">Mechanism-Editor &gt; Add Plane</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Element-Header">Planes</text> define the layout of your machine. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You add <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editors</text> to <text styleclass="Element-Header">Planes</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:36px;"><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif"><caption><![CDATA[How to open the Plane dialog-box]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-AT-EditPlane.ipp" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Edit Plane]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">The <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane </text><text styleclass="Element">dialog</text> opens when you start the <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Plane </text>command. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Body Text">To open the </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane dialog</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> at a different time:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="width:100%;">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">Right-click a </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets"> in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Assembly-Tree</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Click </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Edit-element</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> in the shortcut menu</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="VariableName-IT"><text style="font-style:normal;">OR</text></para>
                <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-How-to-Open-a-Dialog-Box" styleclass="SeeAlso">How to Open a dialog</link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Table">The <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane </text><text styleclass="Element">dialog</text> is now open.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Plane dialog</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:36px;"><text styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">The </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane </text><text styleclass="Element">dialog</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> has two formats, which you can identify by the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Plane Definition</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> parameter.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">The format is a function of the element you select to add the new <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:60px;"><anchor id="PLANE-OFFSET" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2"><keywords><keyword>Plane Definition:<keyword>Offset from Plane</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><caption><![CDATA[ FORMAT 1: Offset from Plane]]></caption><title>Click to exapand /collapse</title></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2" style="vertical-align:bottom;">
          <para styleclass="Body Text">When you select a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text>, the format is <text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Offset from Plane</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:bottom; width:240px;">
          <para styleclass=" " style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><image src="MD-Dialog-AddPlane-Offset.png" scale="-99.90%" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:8pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">New Plane</text><text styleclass="Interface">:</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Parameter">Plane6</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Separator-Header">Plane Parameters</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Plane Definition</text><text styleclass="Body Text">: </text><text styleclass="Parameter">Offset from Plane</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The new <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> is offset along the <text styleclass="VariableName">Z-axis</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> you select.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Element</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">box</text>- the element you select as the reference for the <text styleclass="VariableName">Plane Definition</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName">Parameter to edit</text>:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">&#32;</text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Distance to New Plane</text><text style="font-style:italic;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The offset dimension from the <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> you select and in the <text styleclass="Interface">Element</text> box<image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> to the new <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:bottom; width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-17-Add Plane to Plane.ipp" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[New Plane in the Graphic-Area]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Notes">Notes:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">In the image, the new <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> is <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">offset by the length of the arrow along the Z-axis of the </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane </text><text styleclass="Body Text">you selected</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The X-axis and Y-axis of the new <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text> are collinear with those of the <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text> you selected to add the new <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:60px;"><anchor id="PLANE-ANGLE" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><keywords><keyword>Plane Definition:<keyword>Angle from Line</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><caption><![CDATA[FORMAT 2: Angle from Line]]></caption><title>Click to exapand /collapse</title></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Text">When you select a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Line</text>, or the <text styleclass="VariableName">X-axis</text> or <text styleclass="VariableName">Y-axis</text> of a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text>, the format is <text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Angle from Plane</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:254px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-DIALOG-PLANE-LINE.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Notes">Note</text>: you can select a <text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, or the</text> X-axis or Y-axis of a <text styleclass="Element">Part</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="VariableName"> New Plane:</text>&#32;<text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Plane5</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Separator-Header">Plane Parameters</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Interface2">&#32;</text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Plane Definition</text><text styleclass="Body Text">: </text><text styleclass="Parameter">Angle from Line</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="VariableName"> Element box:</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> The </text>element(s) you select as the reference(s) for the <text styleclass="VariableName">Plane Definition</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Parameters to edit:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-5.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Parameter">&#32;</text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Move Plane to end-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Select to move the origin of the <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> from the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> to the <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text><text styleclass="Parameter">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets"> that is in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Element</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Body Text">box</text><image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Body Text" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="VariableName">X-axis</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> is now from the <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text> to the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Interface2">Note</text><text styleclass="Notes">: </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-style:normal; color:#ff0000;">must</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Parameter">Move Plane to End-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> to add a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-AddGearPair-Bevel" styleclass="Element-Header">Bevel Gear-Pair</link><text styleclass="Element-Header">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Rotational Axes</text></para>
          <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Parameter">Rotate around X-axis</text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;"> :</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> Rotate the new </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> around the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">X-axis</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> direction of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Parameter">Rotate around Y-axis</text> : <text styleclass="Body Text">Rotate the new </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> around the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Y-axis</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> direction of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Parameter">Rotate around Z-axis</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> : Rotate the new </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> around the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Z-axis</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> direction of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes">Notes:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">When you select a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Line</text>, t<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">he </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Origin </text>of the new<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> is coincident with </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">the </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Line&apos;s</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Interface">Start-Point</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2">or<text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, if </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">you enable </text><text styleclass="Parameter">Move Plane to end-Point</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">When you select a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Line</text>, the <text styleclass="Interface2" style="font-size:14pt;">+</text><text styleclass="VariableName">ve X-axis</text> of the new <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text> is in the direction from<text styleclass="HowTo Numbered"> the </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Line&apos;s</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Element">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered"> to </text><text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2">or </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered"> to </text><text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, if you enable </text><text styleclass="Parameter">Move Plane to end-Point</text></para>
